1.title: The New Blood
1.plot: Camp Woodward is back for season two with three new kids: Cody Davis (Skate), Hunter Bagent (BMX) and Larry Schmidt (Skate). Find out all about them before the head off to camp.

2.title: Arrival Day
2.plot: Larry (skate) adjusts to working at camp, while Cody (skate) tries to figure out the best way to bend the rules. Hunter (bmx) finds a slice of home with his older buddy and pro Joe Rich.

3.title: Kids Will Be Kids
3.plot: Larry (skate) adjusts to working at camp, while Cody (skate) tries to figure out the best way to bend the rules. Hunter (bmx) finds a slice of home with his older buddy and pro Joe Rich.

4.title: Competition
4.plot: Cody (skate) demonstrates why he is the next generation of a skater in the Playstation Am Jam. Hunter (bmx) tries new ramps, and Larry (skate) works hill duty and discovers campers sneaking out.

5.title: Frazzled
5.plot: Larry (skate) wakes up "frazzled" and late for dish dog duty. Hunter (bmx) loses his race to his friend and pro Joe Rich but learns something about himself. Cody (skate) gets busted for not wearing pads but still enjoys all the facilities at camp.

6.title: Final Goodbye
6.plot: The campers close out their final days of camp and have tons of fun. Cody (skate), Larry (skate), and Hunter (bmx) all reflect back on their Camp Woodward experience.

1.title: Meet the New Kids
1.plot: Meet the new kids of season four, Chad (BMX), Alex (Skate) and Lucky (Skate). We find out why they are attending the best sports camp, Camp Woodward, in Pennsylvania this summer.

2.title: 1st Day
2.plot: The new kids arrive at Camp Woodward in Pennsylvania. Chad, Alex and Lucky meet up with old friends, meet new friends, participate in a skate/BMX demo, and take a quick trip to the emergency room.

3.title: Midler Down
3.plot: Alex is back from the hospital and sneaks in skate sessions. Chad and Sean are protesting the ban on bikes. Lucky and camp staff argue over safety rules. Featuring skateboarder Renton Millar.

4.title: Rolling with the Homies
4.plot: Chad buys a skateboard and finds hidden talents. Alex tries to impress the older kids and there are paintball attacks.

5.title: Competitive Side
5.plot: Lucky is struggling to meet his skating goals. Alex is working on his first skate film and Chad finds his competitive side. Lucky continues to break the rules and his board is confiscated.

6.title: Age Factor
6.plot: The kids enjoy country life and go horseback riding and river tubing. Alex continues with his antics and Lucky manages to get his board back from the camp counselors.

7.title: Lucky's Heroes
7.plot: Lucky makes peace with camp staff and leads his team to victory in the Pizza Jam contest. Chad has a mission to learn to flair from the top BMX pros. Alex and Sean get into a fight.

8.title: Finale
8.plot: The summer comes to an end; Chad learns his flair, Alex reforms his bad boy ways just in time for his skate film premiere,and Lucky improves his skating skills and becomes a leader.

1.title: Stakes Are High
1.plot: Five seasons of Camp Woodward cast members battle it out and push themselves to the limit for the chance to win an all-expenses paid trip to China.

2.title: Ticket Home
2.plot: Star camper Lucky is sent packing after putting both teams in physical danger; Chad arrives to replace him and Jovon becomes a team player.

3.title: Video Disaster!
3.plot: Disaster hits the Black team when someone deletes their video footage during a skate film contest, and the teams get help from expert builders to design skate obstacles.

4.title: The Wildcard
4.plot: Sean is in danger of being kicked off his team after he gives up during a challenge, and camp owner Gary offers up the option of trading a team member.

5.title: Zane's Big Break
5.plot: Zane struggles to find inspiration for his video project, Chad bails on his team, and everyone continues to work on their skate videos.

6.title: Boiling Point
6.plot: Tensions are high, as two team members get into a fist fight and Maverick makes the decision to send one of the campers home.

8.title: The Video Finale
8.plot: The winner is revealed during a video premiere in front of a huge crowd, and scores a trip to Beijing, China.

2.title: Camp Kick-Off

4.title: Lights, Camera, Action

5.title: Don't Mess with Chuck
5.plot: Frankie tries to avoid getting in trouble.

6.title: All in the Family
6.plot: Johnny gets a special surprise visitor to camp.

7.title: Slice of Life
7.plot: Jacob heads off to compete in the Dew Tour and camp holds the big Pizza Jam.

8.title: Wide World of Woodward
8.plot: Camp wraps and the guys get a surprise they'll never forget.

With a popular video part on The Berrics and interviews in both The Skateboard Mag and Thrasher, CJ is proving to be one of the best park terrain skateboarders in the world.

imdb.plot outline: Camp Woodward isn't your typical summer camp. Silly songs and camp fires are replaced with a chance to ride side by side with the biggest names in skateboarding and BMX at the largest training facilities in the world. For the privileged, a week at Woodward comes easy. For others, the road is paved with saving, sacrifices and for some, the lowly service of "dish duty" to pay the dues. The result is a coming of age reality series where aspiring athletes test their skills during the most important week of their lives. Egos clash and conflicts mount as this year's cast of campers and counselors push each other's limits.
